<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A train-line suburb on Brisbane's northern boundary.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Bald Hills sits at the northern edge of the City of Brisbane on the Pine River, with the train station at the end of the line offering reliable rail access to the CBD. It is a value suburb in the truest sense: families upgrading their block size, first home buyers using the southern Moreton Bay price gap, and investors tracking the broader northern growth corridor all compete here. The suburb's identity is shaped by St Paul's School on the southern side and the river parkland to the north, with Gympie Road providing the main retail and arterial spine.
    </p>
