<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know how to position a Bald Hills property for the buyer most likely to pay the strongest price. The suburb is wide and topographically varied, and the gap between a well-elevated family block on the southern side and a smaller post-war block near the river edge is meaningful. The campaign approach for each is different, and reading the property correctly at the appraisal stage is what makes that difference.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      St Paul's School on Strathpine Road is one of the largest independent schools in Brisbane and creates a draw for families across the broader northern corridor. Bald Hills train station is the terminus of the Caboolture and Sunshine Coast line and the only train-station option for buyers who want to live north of the Gateway Motorway without paying Strathpine prices for the same convenience. The Pine River parkland on the suburb's northern boundary provides walking and cycling links to Bracken Ridge and Carseldine, and the Westfield Strathpine and Aspley Hypermarket retail precincts are both within ten minutes by car. For the right buyer, the combination of block size, train access and the green corridor is unmatched in this price bracket on the northside.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
